# SigScale Inventory Management (sigscale_im)

## Prerequisites
	Install erlang(>18)
	$ sudo apt install erlang-dev erlang-snmp erlang-inets erlang-parsetools
	Install nodejs, nopm and polymer-cli (Ubuntu 16.04)
	$ curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_8.x | sudo -E bash -
	$ sudo apt install nodejs
	$ sudo npm install -g --unsafe-perm polymer-cli

## Building
	$ mkdir ../sigscale_im.build  (create build directory)
	$ cd ../sigscale_im.build     (change working directory for build)
	$ ../sigscale_im/configure    (creates Makefiles)
	$ make                        (builds entire package)
	$ make check                  (run dialyzer and common_test)

## Installing
	$ sudo make install         (installs embedded application in system)

## Cleaning
	$ make clean                (removes files created with make)
	$ make distclean            (removes files created with configure also)

## Options
	$ ../sigscale_im/configure --enable-debug
	$ ../sigscale_im/configure --with-ssl=/opt/local

